Becca would approach people and ask if anyone knew anything, more than she would track.
_...the dice clatter across the table..._
So 2 successes.

She asks after the woman, either describing her or using her name.  One smaller man, with a table of various goods set up on it apparently for "sale" outside a large tent, responds. "Oh, Peregrine - sure.  She's our Scout Leader.  I had heard she just returned.  She's probably either back at her tent or in the War Room."  He points you in the direction of both.

Becca thanks him, then goes in the direction of the War Room. She thinks that it would be awkward for her to invade Peregrine's personal space by going to her tent, and is really hoping she is in the War Room.

She approached a large log-built structure.  In many ways, it's the least cobbled-together looking thing she's seen.  The floor is made from blankets and carpets.  There is a large wooden table in the middle.  There are two women and a large man arguing inside, but at first glance, none are the woman who led them here.
Becca listens in on the argument, waiting clearly by the door. If they notice she is there, she plans to ask them where Peregrine is.

She hears the woman say "Our scouts have not returned.  We are vulnerable - you need to increase the patrols on the borders or we'll take a risk of another attack!"  One of the men says "We just dealt with a wave last night, there's no way they have enough fodder for another one tonight.  We can't spare the people right now.  The scouts will return, and we'll know more.  Be patient."
(Does this structure have a door of any sort, or is it just an opening?)
Its gazebo-esque.  Like four big posts the size of telephone poles and a canvas roof.
Becca raps her hand on one of the posts to announce herself. "Excuse me?"
"I'm looking for Peregrine. Would any of you happen to know where she is?"
They startle, then turn to Becca.  The woman speaks "I've never seen you before. Where have you come from?"
"I was among those that your camp stopped on the road. Me and my companions have only been here for a short time."
Her eyes narrow.  "In that case you know more than I do.  Peregrine was one of whom I was speaking.  she was north of the camp, scouting our borders.  I have not yet seen her."

Becca slumps ever so slightly. "Oh. That doesn't sound good. I'm afraid I am not very good at tracking, or I would offer to help in that way. I do have a question for you, though: why was my group brought here? We didn't mean any harm to your people, and I have traveled that way many times before without any interference."

The woman looks at the men and shrugs, as if saying "any thoughts?".  One of the men says "These have been a very difficult couple of weeks for our pack.  We don't know why you were brought here - under normal circumstances, my best bet would be food *here he grins with two rows of sharpened teeth - it's hard to tell if he's joking or not*.  If Peregrine brought you, she has reasons.  There will be a Meet shortly where I understand we'll learn more.
Becca laughs quietly at the concept of being food for a werewolf, whether the man was joking or not. "Well, thank you anyway. I will be sure to be at the meeting."

Becca leaves and begins to search for the biker werewolf who had arm wrestled her earlier. If she can't get information from the higher-ups, she will at least try and talk to someone who has a chance of knowing what's going on. She can only hope he stayed in the camp after dropping them off.
*Decide how she will approach this.  Again, investigate if she's asking around, survival is more for actively searching*
She would still be asking around, although she would not be asking the leaders. She doesn't want to continue bothering those in the tent.
_...the dice clatter across the table..._
1 success.
Someone recognizes her description.  She is able to find him loudly playing poker outside of a camper near the north side of the camp.
(Of course he is XD)
*waits for Becca to flip the table*
Becca sits near the biker, but not at the table (if they are playing at a table). She isn't really interested in playing, she just wants to talk.

He notices her sit down and jumps up, overturning the table and spilling the contents all over the ground. "Hey!  Everyone, this is the girl!  She's the one I told you about!  Arms like tree trunks!"  He does not seem upset, in fact, he is very excited to see her.
Becca looks at the spilled table in amusement, then looks to the biker with a smile. "Well hello again. I don't believe I ever got your name!"
*looks up his name*
(XD)

He claps her on the back, "And neither did I get yours, but then I don't think we were in any condition to do the asking.  I'm Roaring Waters!  *he points out his three poker buddies, two young men and an older woman, all of whom don't seem phased by him* And this is Evening Sun, Marked Cat, and Walks in Silence."
"Well, it's nice to officially meet you! I'm Becca." Becca offers to shake hands with each of them, using a firm grip that she assumes they will appreciate.
He returns the grip
(I'm not sure what that roll is for and it scares me lol)
Strength
(Ahhhh ok)
He returns the firm grip

Becca looks at Roaring Waters. "Next time you stop by my pub, I think we ought to engage in a less destructive game. Max is still pretty upset about the table." Becca whispers under her breath something about Max not having a right to be upset about the table considering what happened to her door.
He nods, seems a little confused, but it's that kind of look where you don't want people to know you don't know what they're talking about.
(Do the other three at the table look familiar? Like, were they among those who brought us to the camp?)
They do not, complete strangers.
(Ok)
Becca, still looking at Roaring Waters, waves dismissively. "Never mind that for now. Can I speak with you for a few moments about what happened earlier?"
His eyebrows raise.  "The arm wrestling?  Sure!  I'm lucky we weren't betting!."

Becca chuckles. "No, not the wrestling, although that was entertaining. I was talking about the reason I'm here right now. Do you know why me and my friends were brought here? And why it was done so... violently?"

"Brought here?  I thought you came looking for me.  Honestly, I feared for my life for a hot minute." (frankly, the thought of this guy fearing for his life is comical, however, he doesn't appear to be joking)

"No, I mean-" Becca sighs. "We were driving to an appointment, and all of a sudden, you and a handful of other werewolves were running next to my car. Next thing I know, my car has an arrow in its tire, my friends are either shot in the chest or pinned to my car, and my phone has an arrow through it," Becca pulls her broken phone from her pocket for emphasis. "I was wondering if you had any idea why *that* happened."
Becca keeps the knowledge that she intimidates Roaring Waters in the back of her mind.

Oh!  That.  Peregrine asked me to look after you guys.  That's why I was in the Snow Goose in the first place.  Apparently there were some nasty people looking for you.  Then she asked me and the others to follow you to keep track of you.  As for the shooting - All I know is I was asked to not engage.  I don't think she was taking chances until she could talk to you personally.
"Ah. Thanks for telling me. Oh, that reminds me; sorry about how Max snapped at you earlier. He really, really likes his tables. I think he was more mad at me than you, if I'm honest."
He laughs.  I've broken nicer tables."
"I'm sure you have, but that one just happened to be Max's." Becca giggles, looking down at the table that was flipped earlier. "At least this one seems to have survived."
He shrugs it off.  "So, you coming to the Meet?"
"I was planning on it. Not quite sure where it is, though..."
Becca hears the roar. She doesn't know what it is, but hurries to investigate as worry makes her stomach drop.
She is able to find the other two, Zahir on the ground, Max standing.
She hurries to Zahir. "Are you alright? Are you hurt?"

Becca made it down to the car in record time, excited to finally get away from the depressing air that had been following her the entirety of the last night. "Have you ever washed a car by hand before?" she asked Zahir.
"Yea, I used to do it from time to time!" Zahir replied. He continues to folloe Becca, thinking  it was nice to get outside, where it was quiet and peaceful with a small breeze of wind went by.

Becca slipped into the driver's seat of the car and waited until Zahir was in the passenger's seat to keep speaking. "I used to do it with my crew after a particularly bad shift of runs. It always made the mood more relaxed."

"Speaking of the mood... how are you doing with everything that's been going on?"

Zahir got into the passenger seat as he listened to Becca. "Sounds like you guys had good memories together!" Zahir chuckled a little "Mood wise, this has definitely not been easy for any of us. I just know Ian's going to find out eventually...But hey, we all managed to stick together at least!"

"That's true, I suppose." It's clear that Becca hadn't really thought about that as she started the car and began driving to a self-wash station she was familiar with. "And yeah, my time as an EMT was one of the highlights of my life. I remember, one time, Bonnie -one of my partners- and I got into a hose fight when we were cleaning the ambulance. We both got so soaked that we had to change into some of the scrubs in the back before we could go back to the station. We got so many strange looks..." Becca quietly laughed.

"How about you? You have any fun memories from before... all this? You know, before being a vampire and getting stuck in this whole mess?"

Zahir thought for a moment. " Not much, but I do remember when I was really little, my parents would always pull pranks on me, and I felt for every one of them. So by the time my brother's were 5, I tried to recreate one my mom did on me, and Zachary got so scared he punched me in the gut. It hurt but it was still hilarious." Zahir quietly chuckled a little. "I suppose we all have that one memory that keeps us happy."
"Definitely." Becca pulled into the carwash bay and checked that all the windows were closed. "You want to help with this? Fair warning, you'll probably get wet." Mischief twinkled in her eye.
Zahir got a little suspicious but agreed and got out to help wash the car. "You're planning something aren't you.?"
"Hmm... not exactly *planning* anything persay..." Becca chuckled and got out the car, waiting until Zahir got out to pay to start the water.
Zahir struggled it off and made sure all the doors were closed and walked over to Becca, waiting for what she needed him to do
((keep an eye on your time, it's almost second period. I'm good to keep multitasking, but I don't want to get you in trouble))

Becca offered the soaping hose and a pile of change to Zahir. "Once I get to the back corner of the car, start soaping after me. I'll come back around to your side to rinse off the soap once I make it around the car."
"Alright!" After Zahir payed for the car wash, he waited for Becca to get to the back corner and started soaping the car.
Darn auto correct 😅//

Becca continued working around the car, eventually making it back to the soaped section and cleaning it off to reveal the shining paint below. She waited until Zahir was done scrubbing, then took aim with the still-spraying hose, peeking around the car and hitting his ankles with just a bit of water.
Zahir quickly backed away to not get anymore wet and chuckled a bit. "So that's what you meant."
"What do you mean? I totally didn't aim for you!" Becca laughed, peeking around the car again but missing with her second attack.
Zahir noticed what she was trying to do and laughed a little. "I think you missed me!"
"Aw." She shot the water in a wide spray over the car, attempting to mist Zahir. "I better get one good shot in before the water runs out!"
Zahir moved closer to the car so Becca can spay him with the hose. Acting like he has no clue whats going on to make Becca happy. "This car is so shiny, how did I not notice that-"
Becca took aim and hit Zahir in the chest for a brief second, trying to hit him but not soak him completely. "Gotcha!"
Zahir starting laughing "oh no! You got me!" He got on the ground just to add on to the moment.
((oh dude Zahir got soaked doing that, no doubt))
He definitely did 😅//

Becca laughed, turning the hose away just as the water ceased. "Oh come on, now you're going to be soaking wet! Hold on, let me put this away-" Becca went over to the wall hook and put away the water hose, grin still wide across her face. She hurried back over to Zahir and offered a hand to help him up.
Zahir was laughing the whole time as he grabbed onto Becca's hand and got up. "I had to make entertaining!"
Becca froze for a second before reaching her arms out to hug Zahir. "May I?"
Zahir smiled and accepted Becca's hug. "Of course, but I may warn you, you might get a little wet."

Becca chuckled, taking the hug anyway. "Thank you, Zahir. I really needed this. It means a lot." She waited a few moments before pulling away, then took off her now-wet sweater. "Layers are key!" She winked at Zahir with a smile, then skipped over to the driver's side of the car.
Zahir chuckled as he got in the passenger seat. "Soooo, where to now.?"

"Unless you have any other ideas, I was kind of thinking it would be nice to just head back to Max's apartment. We probably shouldn't leave Moonshine alone with Max for too long. Who knows what could happen." Becca half-joked as she started up the car.
"That's true, hopefully Moonshine didn't break anything, or upset Max." He stopped talking there so he wouldn't start ranting.

The mood was lighthearted with a tinge of anticipation as they both made their way back up to Max's apartment and tried to ignore their worries about what was coming, and what had happened while they were gone.

Max was a mess. Well, that was an understatement. While he walked the halls of Cawdor Castle with a blank expression, his mind raced. Everything in his mind was shattering, fractured into thousands of pieces of broken glass that Max kept pushing further into him with each step. As soon as he got back to his room, he finally broke. Max ripped the room apart- anything that wasn't nailed down was destroyed. He was screamed, loud, anguished. No one dare enter the room; not when Max was like this. Any werewolf or ghoul nearby quickly scurried away at the outburst. When the room was barren, with only destroyed splinters of wood and shattered picture frames littering the floor, Max finally crumbled into a pile on the floor. He would have thrown up if it was possible, and the blood from his untreated wounds dribbled to the ground, pooling there. As the noise died down from the room, outside, only the darest braved the halls outside Max's room.

Becca grimaced as she heard the noises finally settle from the room her and Max were temporarily sharing while at the castle. Although she knew something was wrong, she hadn't quite expected *that* reaction. Clearly, she had to try and help, even if her sense of self-preservation was telling her that was a bad idea. Quietly, Becca padded into one of the other rooms in the hallway and snagged a blanket off of one of the beds, reminding herself that she had to be sure it got put back and the bed remade once she was done.

As she walked to the room, she tried to remain calm and collected. This wasn't going to work if she made even the slightest error. Blanket slung over her shoulder, Becca opened the door slowly and walked into the room, giving Max a wide berth. She noted his condition with concern, before settling to the floor at the furthest point she could from where Max's person and his belongings were strewn. She tried to keep her hands within sight at all times, and avoided direct eye contact.
"Hey, Max."

Max's ear's twitched at the sound of Becca entering the room. From his curled-up position on the floor, his eyes locking onto her moving figure, his gaze like that of a rabid animal. His figure shook slightly as she approached, even if she didn't get close. It wasn't of fear though, no, that familiar tensing of muscles, anyone could see he was ready to go on the defensive at any second. It was almost like he didn't even recognize her until she spoke, her soft voice filling his ears. 

At first, Max said nothing. She had seen him like *this*, broken, unstable, though by this point, who even cares?? The whole castle already thought him a monster, if not before, definitely now by his outburst. Keira did. ***Keira hated him***, oh god, she hit him, it was all his fault. 

***"YOU LEFT US!! YOU'RE A COWARD!!" ***

The words spun in his head as he stared Becca down. God, Becca must have hated him. Keira was right. He is a coward; a selfish, disgusting coward, a monster. He'd almost killed Moonshine, he would have if Becca never stood up to him. And now he's laying on the floor, in a pool of his own blood, looking up to one of the most forgiving people he's ever met. If Ian had ever known about Max's violent outbursts, he would surely be staked by now, left to rot in a decrepit basement. 

But when he looked into Becca's eyes, he didn't see any judgment, or anger, or disgust. No, Becca's eyes were filled with only compassion, worry, with a presence that could only be described as one thing. 

*~~Safe.~~*

Becca smiled slightly in relief at Max's voice. He was still coherent enough to recognize her, that was good. With how much stress the whole team had been experiencing recently, she had been worried that the sound of breaking objects in the room had connected directly to the shattering of any last senses of control Max had. This, though; she could work with this.

The direct method had not worked in the past, Becca recognized now as she considered her next moves. As much as she desperately wanted to rush over to Max and smother him in the blanket she had brought, she knew better now. Instead, she opted to let him open up to her in his own timing.

"You can tell me whatever you need, Max, and I'll do anything I can to help. If you want me to just sit here, I can do that. If you want me to come over and give you this blanket I brought, I can do that, too. Whatever you need."

With that, Becca leaned back against the wall behind her and began quietly humming. The move was Max's, now. All she could do was wait for him to decide how much help he wanted.
"...Why are you *here*, Becca?"
((Oh man, many responses I could pick from here))
((Give me a few moments to pray and I'll be back to craft a response))
((Yeye))

"I'm here because I care about you, Max. You're a part of the team I promised to take care of, and I don't take that commitment lightly. You matter, and right now my instincts are telling me that you need someone to show you that." Becca offered, still speaking gently.
Max laughed, it sounded almost shrill and his voice cracked half way through. "You didn’t promise to take care of me Becca, Ian took advantage of the situation and I stayed."
"It's not worth it you know. In the end, I'll either drag you all down with me or I'll abandon you all."
((Oh boy, this requires a complicated and emotionally sensitive response))
((Yup lmao
((Fingers crossed I can get Becca's thoughts out correctly here))
((You got this Loen!))

"I don't believe that. First of all, when Ian pushed you onto me, I could have said no. As I got to know you, though, I saw a lot of myself and decided I was going to try and do anything I could to help you. I gave you my friendship in that decision, Max. Ian had no say in that choice." Becca shuffled a little bit on the floor, and pulled the arms of her sweater down over her hands in a subconscious movement.

Becca gave a pause, considering her next words carefully. A tear slipped out of her eye unbidden, and she wiped it away stubbornly.

"And I have to believe you are worth my care. Because if you aren't, then I sure as heck am not worth anyone else's, either. I pose just as much of a risk as you do, or any other member of the team. Heck, I almost just got Zahir-" Becca shuddered, "*killed*."
((Oh please let this response work the way I want it to))

"I don't hold any illusions that we are a perfect team, Max. But if I cast out anyone who has any flaws, any weaknesses, any downfalls, I would not only lose everyone I've ever cared about, but I would also lose myself."

Max watched Becca as she spoke, moving to a sitting position. His movements were stiff and hesitant, but he waited for her to finish speaking. And when she did, he could only look at her. 

What should he say; what could he say? Max knew better than the rest of the team that Becca wasn't perfect. So many times she had been open and vulnerable with him, and this time was no different. 

Apart of Max saw it as weakness; by letting everyone in and taking risks, one would only destroy themselves as each person let in ripped that person to shreds. 

Max was closed off, he knew that, he was supposed to be. The unfeeling, quiet, solider who would do anything for the mission. But that was never him, was it? No, the person he was before the team, before Ian, would have been horrified with who he had become. 

Maybe that was a good thing. 

Maybe it wasn't. 

He didn't know. 

All Max knew was that he was just tired. 

He was so, so, tired. 

So he did the only thing his brain was telling him to do. 

He wrapped his arms around Becca, and he began to weep.
((YESSSS))

The sudden hug startled Becca, but she automatically returned the embrace and let her own tears fall in tandem with Max's. She realized with a start just how emotionally exhausted she had become, hiding most of her anxiety behind masks that were finally starting to fall. She hadn't quite known how much she had missed a friendly hug. Her arms cautiously tightened around Max, attempting to avoid his injuries even as she tried to draw him in as close as she could to reassure herself that everything would be okay.

"It seems I came to offer you support and managed to drag out my own insecurities." Becca murmured with a watery giggle, leaning into Max's solid warmth.

Max didn't let her go as he spoke. "I think you can multitask." He said quietly. "...You might need to get a new sweater, Beccs..." He added after a moment of seeing the shoulder of her current on stained with his blood and tears.

Becca smiled a little, "Don't worry, I'm sure it will wash out like it always does. This sweater was a gift from my mom. I don't know what she used to make it, but it seems to repel every kind of stain I throw at it. I probably should get a different one to wear out on missions though, I'm worried that someday my luck with it will run out."

Becca carefully pulled her head away from Max's own shoulder to look at the gashes on his face, sorrow crossing her own. She couldn't even imagine what he had said to Peregrine to cause that kind of reaction to be warranted. Her one hand reached up and ghosted across the side of his face, careful to avoid the wounds as she let concern and curiosity show in her expression.

Max didn't move from her hand and let Becca inspect the gashes. "... I used to know her, before Ian... but... when I didn't come back..." He trailed off. He knew his choice would hurt her and Sal and Valarie, but he NEVER imagined that it would be this bad.
"Did you have a choice? To go back, I mean." Becca had a hard time believing that Max would ever purposely hurt someone if it wasn't strategically the best choice overall.

"...Ian said I could become his right hand, or I could die. That was my choice. I had hope for a bit that I would be able to escape if I was careful enough... but..." Max closed his eyes. "...Ian had this... connection... with me. If he said my name, I would have no choice but to follow. Not to mention, he was supposed to be keeping my sister *safe,* and whenever I asked for updates he assured me that she was fine...Now she's missing, and Keira is a werewolf and Sal is *dead.*..Maybe it would have been better if I agreed to die..."

Becca tightened her arm around Max, trying to be brave. Trying not to remember her own depression after her parents had died. "*No*. You can't think like that, Max. Ian manipulated you. Hurt you. You can't blame yourself for the damage he did."

Becca hesitated, trying to settle her own emotions. "For what it's worth... I think you made the right decision. Whether you lived or died, your friends could have and probably would have suffered the same fate. But your survival has helped save me and the team time and time again, where we probably would have failed without you. I have no doubt that you've saved my life, Max, and for that, I owe you infinite thanks."

Max could tell her that she was wrong, that he was truly awful and that without him here they'd never been in half of this mess. But Max had always been a little selfish, so he only nodded and held on to her.
((I went to play Beat Saber to briefly escape the feels and dear me did they come rushing back the second I returned))

Even though she was hesitant to bring it up, she knew she needed to.

"I'm sorry for my behavior the last couple of days, by the way. I feel bad for doubting your judgement, but I had to try and do *something*. I didn't mean to get you or any of the others hurt in the process." Becca reburied her face in Max's shoulder, guilt surging through her. If Max was going to work so well with her, he was definitely at least owed an apology.

"It’s alright, I understand why you did it. I forgive you." Even if Max thought it a bit nonsensical for Becca to apologize for caring about someone, he figured she needed to hear that as much as he needed a shoulder to cry on.
"Thank you," Becca whispered, finally able to fully relax. *Max forgave her*. That little miracle alone was enough to make it all worth it.
!!!RP END, ROOM OPEN!!!

Becca knew she had to talk to the new guy at some point. She felt kind of bad that he had helped Moonshine escape from the mage school and she hadn't even gotten the chance to thank him yet. And now he was at the castle, among strangers- overall, probably not a great experience for... Goryo, was it? Becca had barely even caught the poor guy's name.

Thankfully, she had seen which room he had been assigned to in the castle upon arrival. She couldn't be sure he was actually there, but she had to try and see if she could talk to him. Aside from the fact that not knowing him was probably a security threat (after all, inviting a random ninja mage that they knew nothing about into the castle? Definitely not the best idea they had ever come up with), she genuinely wanted to get to know him better.

She strolled up to what she knew was Goryo's door, letting her excitement at meeting a potential new team member overwhelm her fear. Then, after a moment of hesitation, Becca raised her hand to the door, and knocked.

Goryo would hear the knock on the door and opened it. He was wearing a black tee shirt and pants at the moment, and he seemed a bit weaker than when she had first saw him. His wakizashi was sheathed and stood against a table in the room, and his Katana was unsheathed and looked to have been recently sharpened. Overall, he seemed to be making himself at home between the shifts he would take upon himself to help make sure none of the zombies could get into the castle grounds, and to help dispatch those that did.

In the bulk of the time he had been spending there so far, he had been pattern scouring to recover mana, since that was the only consistent mana source he had access to for the moment. But considering his other options, he knew he was better off weakening himself a bit for a few days than looking for tass or a hallow when there was a zombie horde outside. He would reach out his hand to offer a handshake.

"I never had an opportunity to properly  introduce myself. My name is Goryo."

"It's nice to meet you properly, Goryo! I wanted to check in, make sure you're doing alright? I know it's been really busy, and I didn't get a chance to get to know you before we just kind of dragged you into this. It's been pretty chaotic." Becca smiled a little, taking the hand offered firmly.

He would shake her hand.

"It's nice to meet you properly too! I have generally been doing pretty well, despite how chaotic things have been. Honestly, you all showed up at almost the perfect time. I think I was at best a few hours away from my cover being blown."

Becca pondered for a moment. "Your cover?" She didn't remember him mentioning anything about that when they had gotten Moonshine out, although with the speed that everything went down, she could have forgotten.

It took him a moment to realize that he had forgotten to tell anyone why he was there.

"I must have forgot to mention, I was on a mission from the guardians of the veil to investigate a woman in the mage school under the suspicions that she was actually a vampire. I had to pretend to work for her for a while, and her plans seem to be what caused this zombie outbreak. And I think she was moments away from... what was the term she used?.... diablerizing your friend."
